HTTP_TRIGGER_MSG: A Nuclio function must have a single HTTP trigger. You can define such a trigger here. Otherwise, when deploying the function a default HTTP trigger named "default-http" is defined and deployed automatically unless there is a custom HTTP trigger configuration in the external source code.

ONBUILD_IMAGE_DESCRIPTION: The name of an "onbuild" container image from which to build the function's processor image; the name can include {{ .Label }} and {{ .Arch }} for formatting
OVERWRITE_FUNCTION_MESSAGE: A newer version of the function is already deployed. Deploying your version will overwrite the newer version. Alternatively, cancel the deployment, refresh the UI to get the latest version, make your changes again, and redeploy.

CONFIG_MAP.HEAD: Kubernetes ConfigMap
CONFIG_MAP.REST: for storing configuration artifacts separately from the container image content

TOOLTIP.DEPLOY_INVALID_CONFIG: Invalid config, cannot deploy (review the tabs and fix invalid fields)

TOOLTIP.DISABLED_FUNCTION: Only running functions can be tested

GITHUB.BRANCH: The GitHub repository branch from which to download the function code
GITHUB.TOKEN: A GitHub access token for download authentication
GITHUB.URL: The URL of the GitHub repository that contains the function code
GITHUB.WORK_DIR: The relative path to the function-code directory within the configured repository branch (default: "/" — the root directory)

TOOLTIP.GPU_LIMIT: Maximum number of GPUs per replica. Note that while the function is enabled it monopolizes the allocated GPUs even when they're not in use.
TOOLTIP.IMAGE_NAME: The name of the function’s container image
TOOLTIP.INACTIVITY_WINDOW: Applicable only when setting the minimum number of replicas to 0
TOOLTIP.INTERVAL_SCHEDULE_ONLY_ONE: Either "Schedule" or "Interval" could be filled, not both, not none

LABELS.HEAD: Kubernetes labels
LABELS.REST: for specifying object attributes that are meaningful and relevant to users

TOOLTIP.NO_INTERNET_ACCESS: Use local Docker images rather than pulling from remote
TOOLTIP.PREFIXED_NAME: {{name}} keys are composed of an optional prefix and a name, separated by a forward slash (/) — '<key prefix>/<key name>'.
TOOLTIP.REDIRECT_UNAUTHORIZED_REQUESTS: This option should be used if the API endpoint is used by GUI. It will redirect the application to the login screen upon unauthorized request.

S3.BUCKET: The name of the S3 bucket that contains the archive file
S3.ITEM_KEY: The relative path to the archive file within the bucket
S3.REGION: The AWS Region of the configured bucket; implicitly deduced if not provided
S3.SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: An S3 secret access key for download authentication
S3.SESSION_TOKEN: An S3 session token for download authentication
S3.WORK_DIR: The relative path to the function-code directory within the extracted archive-file directory (default: "/" — the root directory)
S3.ACCESS_KEY_ID: An S3 access key ID for download authentication

TOOLTIP.TARGET_CPU: Applicable only when minimum and maximum number of replicas are not empty, are not equal to each other, and the maximum is greater than 1
TOOLTIP.TO_MAKE_FUNCTION_ACCESSIBLE: To make the function accessible outside of the cluster, go to the Triggers tab and configure an HTTP trigger with an ingress
TOOLTIP.URL: A URL for downloading the archive file
TOOLTIP.V3IO: A directory in an Iguazio Data Science Platform data container
TOOLTIP.V3IO_ACCESS_KEY: An Iguazio Data Science Platform access key
TOOLTIP.V3IO_STREAM_CONTAINER:
Select a container name of the local platform from the dropdown menu, and the URL will be auto-filled for you.
Advanced: you can manually enter a container name and a URL for remote configuration.
TOOLTIP.V3IO_STREAM_URL:
In case you selected a container name of the local platform from the dropdown menu — do not edit this field.
Advanced: you can manually enter a container name and a URL for remote configuration.
TOOLTIP.VOLUMES: Volumes that define data paths and the required information for accessing the data from the function
TOOLTIP.ALWAYS_WAIT_FOR_READINESS_TIMEOUT_EXPIRA: Wait for the expiration of the readiness timeout period even if the deployment fails or isn't expected to complete before this period expires.
TOOLTIP.WORK_DIR: The relative path to the function-code directory within the extracted archive-file directory (default: "/" — the root directory)
